REMAIN
•
I am the vine; you are the branches. If you REMAIN in me and I in you, you will bear much fruit; apart from me you can do nothing. ‭‭John‬ ‭15:5
‬•
I looked up the word that was staring me down. REMAIN means to stay, carry on, endure, persist, prevail, survive, wait.
•
All of those words indicate a certain amount of tension. This will require commitment and choice. I wanted to see something that said pleasant, easy, second nature.
•
I love when one word stands out like this and I have to sit with it. What word or scripture are you sitting with today?

Know your worth. We often get placed in certain situations where we often forget what we deserve and let the way we feel ambush our thoughts and decisions. Step back from the situation, analyze and remind yourself what you deserve. Being selfless has its time and place but remember, you can't pour from an empty cup. Take care of you first, figure out what you deserve and accept nothing less. Nobody is going to love you as much as the way you love yourself and when you put in more than you get, you're going to get hurt but by remembering what you deserve and taking the necessary steps ensuring you get what you deserve will be for the better. You don't know what you have until it's gone so water your plants before they die.
